    "title": "LESSON 9: COMMONLY MISUSED WORDS",
    "header_color": "green",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "Some English words do not mean what most",
          "people think they mean.",
          "",
          "'Literally' means it actually, truly",
          "happened. It is not a word for 'very.' If",
          "nobody died, do not say you literally died.",
          "",
          "'Ironic' means the opposite of what you",
          "expected happened. Rain on your wedding is",
          "unfortunate, not ironic.",
          "",
          "'Bemused' means confused and puzzled. It",
          "does not mean the same as amused.",
          "",
          "The cards in this cluster teach the real",
          "meaning of twenty such words."
        ],
